@node REQ "Reqirements"


Music Act v1.0 beta reqires at last:

an AMIGA with 68020 CPU
(but it's written in Blitz2 and maybe slow on slow CPU's)
Kickstart v2 or higher
Workbench v2 or higher

And it's logical reqired that you have an cli-player for your song-formats
and songs for playing ;-).


Music Act v1.0 beta is testet and coded on the following AMIGA-system:


AMIGA 1200 HD
CPU 68030 28MHz + FPU
Kickstart v3 (40.68)
Workbench v3 (40.42)

coded in Blitz2 (v2.1)


@endnode
@node CLI / Tooltypes "CLI"

Music-Act offers the feature to load an playlist by starting Music Act.



By starting from CLI, simply add the path and filename of the playlist.

Example:   HD0:>MUSIC-ACTv1.0b SYS:MUSIC-ACT/TEST.MAL



By starting from Workbench visit the icon-info and  add  STARTLIST  as
tooltype and/or the path and filename as tooltype-value.

Example:   STARTLIST=SYS:MUSIC-ACT/TEST.MAL

If  you  add the tooltype only (not the path and filename), after starting,
Music Act will open an filerequester and you  can  choose  a  playlist.  If
you  have choosen  a  playlist, Music Act will play this one and add the
playlist path and filename to your icon-info and save them when you exit
Music Act.

If you cancel the filerequester (waked up by the tooltype STARTLIST!) and
you work with Music Act - loading a playlist, adding items and so on - Music
Act will add the last path and playlist-filename to your icon-info when
you exit.

You  can  delete  the  auto-start  option  by  editing  the icon-info on
your Workbench by deleting the STARTLIST tooltype.


@endnode
@node MAINWIN "MAIN window"

START / STOP        :       Start an item or a list to play.
                            Pressing again stops the current item or list.


JUMP TO NEXT        :       After pressing START / STOP  Music Act  jumps
                            to the next item in the list and you can play
                            this item by pressing START / STOP.

RANDOM JUMP         :       After pressing START / STOP  Music Act  jumps
                            to a randomly calculated item in the list and
                            you can play this item by pressing START / STOP.

USE REQUEST         :       In this option an requester takes the job of the
                            START / STOP gadget, and you can use your
                            keyboard by pressing [y] or [n] to start or stop
                            a song or list.

LOCK-GUI PLAY       :       This locks all gadgets. Only the START / STOP
                            gadget works. (It's useful for live-acts that no
                            false gadgets will be pressed and the act will
                            be breaked.)


ADD ITEM            :       Choose a song with an filerequester and add them
                            to the end of the list.

INSERT ITEM         :       Choose a song with an filerequester and insert
                            them to the activ choosen position by selecting
                            the item after the item that should be inserted.

DELETE ITEM         :       Delete the activ choosen item by selecting the
                            item.

@{"ITEM PREFS" link PREFS}

ADD LIST            :       You can add a saved LIST/PREFS file by choosing
                            with an requester at the end of the list.
                            All player prefs will not be loaded.

INSERT LIST         :       You can add a saved LIST/PREFS file by choosing
                            with an requester in the currently selected item
                            position.


LOAD LIST/PREFS     :       Load the list with the player prefs from
                            disk by using a requester.

SAVE LIST/PREFS     :       Save the list with the player prefs to the
                            disk by using a requester.

@endnode


@node PREFS "ITEM PREFS window"

<song>              :       Here you can visit and edit the activ item
                            with the path.

PLAYER              :       You can visit and edit the path and command
                            line for the player that is choosen for the
                            song.


USE PLAYER 1,2,3,4  :       Use this for selecting 1 of the 4 maybe choosen
                            and edited players (command line) for the activ
                            item.


PLAYER 1,2,3,4      :       You can visit and edit the player and his
                            command line for start and stop.
                            See the tips written in the window for editing.

?                   :       Choose an path and player for 1 of the 4 players.

@endnode
@node HTU "How to use"

Choose  ITEM  PREFS  and choose and edit your needed players and the command
line. Exit ITEM PREFS by pressing the exit window gadget on the window.

Maybe add, insert or delete items by pressing the gadgets.

Select an item by pressing on it in the list and choose ITEM PREFS.
Select then the player for the selected item by pressing USE PLAYER 1,2,3 or 4.

Choose  a play method. Maybe select JUMP TO NEXT and USE REQUESTER. Now, if you
pressing START / STOP Music Act plays your selected or first item  and  opens  a
Requester that ask you for playing the next song or stopping the list. (The
current song will be stopped when you start the next song by pressing yes in
the requester.)


Test the software to check the possibilties and how it works.
@endnode
@node HIW "How it works"

Music Act executes different choosen music-player and plays the songs written in
a list.

You can choose how the play-act will run. You can choose  in  what  series  the
songs  will  be  played.  You  can  play  randomly,  in a next-series or only by
selection the item in the list.

For executing the player and so the song in the list you have the possibility
to choose the start-way. Start songs by use a gadget or a requester.


@endnode
